description:
### Parking Cost

A parking lot charges $0.20 per 10 minutes. The first half an hour is free. From the moment at which 30 minutes have passed, each started 10 minutes interval costs $0.20. Starting from the one at which first two hours have passed, each started 10 minutes interval costs $0.40.

Input: Two strings, timeIn and timeOut, each of them representing a time in 24-hour format ('HH:MM')
Output: Return an integer, the cost (in number of cents) of parking.

Example:

```js parkingCost('14:11', '14:39') // 0 ```
